docs.abstract: Greg Glassman, who started a fitness movement that’s grown for decades, spun CrossFit into a disaster in just days.
docs.snippet: Greg Glassman, who started a fitness movement that’s grown for decades, spun CrossFit into a disaster in just days.
docs.lead_paragraph: Greg Glassman, the founder and chief executive of CrossFit, announced on Tuesday evening he would step down from his role. The resignation comes after days of turmoil for the company.

headline.main: CrossFit Gym C.E.O. Greg Glassman Steps Down in Chaos
headline.print_headline: CrossFit’s C.E.O. Is Out After Tense Exchange

docs.abstract: Gundy’s players threatened a boycott when he wore a shirt promoting One America News Network.
docs.snippet: Gundy’s players threatened a boycott when he wore a shirt promoting One America News Network.
docs.lead_paragraph: Mike Gundy, the winningest football coach in Oklahoma State’s history, apologized on Tuesday after he stirred outrage by wearing a T-shirt with the logo of a right-wing cable channel that aired commentary calling the Black Lives Matter movement “a farce.”

headline.main: Oklahoma State’s Gundy Apologizes for Wearing Shirt of Right-Wing Channel
headline.print_headline: Oklahoma State Coach Gives Apology for Right-Wing Shirt

docs.abstract: The former governor has faltered in a primary campaign for a seat that is essential for Democrats to capture if they hope to retake the Senate majority.
docs.snippet: The former governor has faltered in a primary campaign for a seat that is essential for Democrats to capture if they hope to retake the Senate majority.
docs.lead_paragraph: KREMMLING, Colo. — For months, Democrats have figured that Colorado’s U.S. Senate race, a linchpin of their strategy to take back the majority in November, was essentially in the bag, with the Republican incumbent Cory Gardner trailing by double digits behind their candidate John Hickenlooper, the well-liked and well-known former two-term governor and Denver mayor.

headline.main: Hickenlooper Stumbles in Colorado Race, Complicating Democrats’ Senate Push
headline.print_headline: Hickenlooper Hits Unexpected Turbulence in Colorado Senate Race

docs.abstract: The Africa Center posted the Black Lives Matter sign as cultural organizations across the city offered programming in the spirit of the holiday.
docs.snippet: The Africa Center posted the Black Lives Matter sign as cultural organizations across the city offered programming in the spirit of the holiday.
docs.lead_paragraph: Six-foot letters filled 16 windows of the Africa Center on Friday as the side of the center’s home, a Robert A.M. Stern-designed building in Harlem, became a canvas that spelled out “Black Lives Matter.”

headline.main: A Sign, Rising 45 Feet, Heralds the Juneteenth Holiday in New York

docs.abstract: Companies like YouTube, Condé Nast and Vice addressed systemic inequality and economic uncertainty while showcasing their new offerings to advertisers.

headline.main: As Facebook Boycott Grows, Advertisers Grapple With Race
headline.print_headline: Advertisers Grapple With Race and Economic Uncertainty

docs.abstract: Some demonstrators, and in some cases the police, have paused to kneel, recalling the manner of George Floyd’s death and the gesture by Colin Kaepernick.
docs.snippet: Some demonstrators, and in some cases the police, have paused to kneel, recalling the manner of George Floyd’s death and the gesture by Colin Kaepernick.
docs.lead_paragraph: It is a simple gesture, swaddled in outrage and long-endured grief, that gained powerful currency through the protest against police brutality and racial injustice led by quarterback Colin Kaepernick on the fields of the National Football League.

docs.abstract: Dreamers, and all Americans, deserve more stability than they are getting under Donald Trump.
docs.snippet: Dreamers, and all Americans, deserve more stability than they are getting under Donald Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Thursday, the Supreme Court ruled, by a narrow majority, that the Trump administration could not immediately shut down Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals, a program that protects about 700,000 young immigrants known as Dreamers from deportation.

headline.main: What the Country Needs, on DACA and So Much More
headline.print_headline: The DACA Ruling Affects Us All

docs.abstract: Blocks from where George Floyd drew his last breaths, residents have vowed to avoid the police to protect people of color. The commitment is hard to keep.

docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — When Shari Albers moved three decades ago into Powderhorn Park, a tree-lined Minneapolis neighborhood known as a haven to leftist activists and bohemian artists like herself, she went to work sprucing it up.

headline.main: A Minneapolis Neighborhood Vowed to Check Its Privilege. It’s Already Being Tested.
